g.text: A web crawler is a program that automatically traverses the web by downloading web pages
and following links from one page to another. It is used to index the web for search engines,
collect data for research, or monitor websites for changes.
- Design a web crawler to extract text data from the web and store it to train an LLM
- Your crawler can run for only 5 days
- Crawl the full web starting from seed urls
